value.0: Stoic, poised, and dedicated, the masked Temple Guards of the Jedi Order are a well-honored sect of anonymous warriors sworn to defend Jedi temples with their lives.

The path of the Jedi is one of harmony with the world around them, seeking to serve and channel the will of the Force, as well as protect the denizens of the wider galaxy.

Those who would become known as Jedi Sages pursue this noble goal through the search of lost knowledge, and advancement of the Jedi Order's overall understanding of both the Force and the galaxy in general. They are archivists, explorers, and mystics, particularly potent at unravelling dark schemes and opposing the Sith.

The Jedi Temple Guards are a special sect of Jedi sworn to guardianship over not only the Order but over locales deemed sacred or integral to the balance of the Force. The sect is shrouded deep in mystery, its members leaving behind their past names and identities entirely to serve its cause as faceless defenders.

Beyond temple grounds, the activities of the Temple Guards are highly classified, but what few rumors the Jedi indulge in speak of everything from routine scouting, to spying and infiltration of potential enemies.
The Chef of the place, don't even try to challenge him! He takes his cooking very seriously.

Quiet the mind and the soul will speak.

Meditation is not about stopping thoughts, but recognizing that we are more than our thoughts and our feelings.
